{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix monitoring periodicity offset handling in SearchSpace configuration\n\n### Summary\nThe `set_monitoring_periodicity_offset` function in the NR MAC layer was not properly validating input parameters, leading to unexpected behavior when invalid periodicity or offset values were passed. This caused issues during SearchSpace configuration where the monitoring pattern was not set correctly.\n\nThe root cause was missing input validation that allowed invalid parameter combinations to pass through without proper error handling. Additionally, the function lacked clear documentation on expected parameter ranges and valid values.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: Added input validation for period (must be > 0) and offset (must be < period for period > 1)\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: Added function documentation with valid parameter ranges\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: Added explanatory comment for period=1 case\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: Improved error messages to include actual invalid values\n\n"
}